We yelled a bit when she first started moving (didn't know if she was coming at us or not), but then talked in normal voices as she trotted away.

Puma.name: 5M
Comments: Approached from a lava escarpment and saw 5M from ~60 m away. He was in a gully below us at the base of lava escarpments. He was feeding on the elk. Observed him undetected for ~5 mins then slowly started the descent towards the elk. We got close and weren't stealthy, talking, footsteps made noise, but weak wind was blowing from his direction towards us. He still didn't detect us until we got to ~15 m from him. He looked at us for ~4 seconds, low growl then walked fast away in an opposite direction from us and up a vegetated lava escarpment. He didn't stop to look back, continued on, lost visual when he was ~40 m away.
